TL;DR people misuse chemical imbalance rhetoric to deny that most people would be happy and thriving in different material conditions. But it is critical to know what the different neurotransmitters do if you are mentally ill or neurodivergent (acquired or congenital).

At other times, I also experience a lack of norepinephrine because my adrenals are all worn out for the moment, and then I have absolutely no executive function. Norepinephrine is needed to transport dopamine to the prefrontal cortex (decision maker).

I cannot therapise my way out of my chronic fight or flight response: I know because I tried for 5 years and did CBT, DBT and EMDR. (The last actually helped with my nonexistent autobiographical memory) I need clonidine to block norepinephrine and get my HR under control.

that accompanies things like sex, tasty food, rewarding hobbies or people you enjoy the company of. For most of my life I did not get enough dopamine from these things to know what the fuss was about.

If you give someone too much serotonin? nausea, excessive sleepiness. block its effects completely and they get insomnia and depression. Remove enough dopamine: stiffness and neuromuscular dysfunction. Add it, and muscle control returns. So does the pleasure and enjoyment ...
